# Email Verification API Tests
# VS Code REST Client extension required

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### 1. Register New User (Requires Email Verification)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "retype_password": "password123"
}

### 2. Try to Login with Unverified Email (Should Fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Verify Email with Code
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "code": "123456"
}

### 4. Login After Email Verification (Should Success)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 5. Resend Verification Code
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### 6. Verify Email with Wrong Code (Should Fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "code": "999999"
}

### 7. Verify Email with Expired Code (Wait 10 minutes)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "code": "123456"
}
